    1. Sabse Pehle Core Concept Samajh

👉 Socket.IO me sirf 2 main cheeze hoti hain:

Object	Meaning------------
io	--- Server (poora system)
socket ---	Ek single user connection


 *  CORE CONCEPT:
 * Socket.IO me sirf 2 main cheeze hoti hain:
 * 
 * 1. io     → Server (poora system)
 * 2. socket → Ek single user connection
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 *  GOLDEN RULE:
 * 
 * on   = sunna (listen karna)
 * emit = bhejna (send karna)
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 * ✅ SIRF YE 4 COMBINATION VALID HAIN:
 * 
 * 1. io.on()
 *    → Server kisi event ko sun raha hai
 *    Example:
 *    io.on("connection", (socket) => {})
 * 
 * 2. socket.on()
 *    → Ek particular user se event sunna
 *    Example:
 *    socket.on("send_message", (data) => {})
 * 
 * 3. socket.emit()
 *    → Sirf usi user ko message bhejna
 *    Example:
 *    socket.emit("receive_message", data)
 * 
 * 4. io.emit()
 *    → Sabhi users ko broadcast
 *    Example:
 *    io.emit("user_online", data)
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 * ❌ INVALID / GALAT SYNTAX:
 * 
 * emit.socket() ❌
 * emit.io() ❌
 * on.socket() ❌
 * on.io() ❌
 * emit.on() ❌
 * on.emit() ❌
 * 
 * 👉 Rule:
 * Function hamesha object ke baad aata hai
 * ✔️ socket.emit()
 * ❌ emit.socket()
 * 

--------------------------------------------------
 1. Sabse Important Concept

👉 Jab ye line chal rahi hai:

socket.emit("receive_message", data);

👉 Ye socket kaun hai?

➡️ Ye current connected user ka socket hai
➡️ Jo abhi ye event trigger kar raha hai

 2. Real Meaning

👉 socket.emit() ka matlab:

“jis user ne ye request bheji hai, usi ko response bhejo”
-------------------------------------
---  Final Line (Golden Understanding)

👉 socket.emit() kabhi bhi random user ko nahi jata
👉 hamesha:

"jis user ka socket hai, usi ko"
------------------------------------------------------------------

 *  EXTRA IMPORTANT METHODS:
 * 
 * 1. io.to(socketId).emit()
 *    → kisi specific user ko send
 *    Example:
 *    io.to("abc123").emit("msg", data)
 * 
 * 2. socket.broadcast.emit()
 *    → sabko bhejo except sender
 *    Example:
 *    socket.broadcast.emit("msg", data)
 * 
 * 3. socket.broadcast.to(id).emit()
 *    → specific user ko bhejo but sender ko nahi
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 *  REAL FLOW EXAMPLE:
 * 
 * Scenario:
 * user1 → message bhejta hai user2 ko
 * 
 * Step 1: listen
 * socket.on("send_message", (data) => {})
 * 
 * Step 2: send to receiver
 * io.to(receiverSocketId).emit("receive_message", data)
 * 
 * Step 3: sender ko bhi show
 * socket.emit("receive_message", data)
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 *  EASY MEMORY TRICK:
 * 
 * "Server (io) sabko dekhta hai,
 *  user (socket) apna kaam karta hai"
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 *  QUICK TABLE:
 * 
 * server start           → io.on()
 * user se sunna         → socket.on()
 * ek user ko bhejna     → socket.emit()
 * sabko bhejna          → io.emit()
 * specific user         → io.to().emit()
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 *  VISUAL:
 * 
 *         io (Server)
 *        /    |     \
 *   socket1 socket2 socket3
 * 
 * io.emit()        → sabko
 * socket.emit()    → sirf ek
 * io.to().emit()   → kisi ek specific
 * 
 * -------------------------------
 *  FINAL SUMMARY:
 * 
 * on   = receive
 * emit = send
 * 
 * io     = sab users
 * socket = ek user
 * 
 * ================================
 */
